{
  "stem": "24163.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And all of a sudden, a truck stopped in front of me, and all the Stormtroopers piled out.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And I stood like I was glued to the sidewalk.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I didn't look particularly Jewish, so I-- I wasn't-- I was afraid, and I was not afraid, because no-- this was not the town I was born and raised in, so I didn't think anybody would know me.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "They piled out and walked right into a clothing store, which was owned by a Jewish family.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I even remember the name of the store to this day.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "It was called Haus der Minden.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "They piled into that store.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "They had, like, steel rods with them and wooden planks.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And they smashed the windows in the store, and they dragged the clothing out.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And one stormtrooper would take one pants leg, another one would take another pants leg, and they would rip these suits, the-- the two sleeves apart, two pants apart.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And they threw it all out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And more and more people gathered around me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "As a matter-- there was a German streetcar conductor next to me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "He said, [SPEAKING GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "He-- he said, they're crazy.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "They should give this to poor people.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "They shouldn't tear it apart, he said.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "He didn't-- the logic in his mind was not that they did this to the Jews.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "That, he probably didn't even to object to.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "The very fact he objected that they were destroying something he would have liked to have had, rather than have it destroyed.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "Well then, slowly, I [? ebbed ?] out of the crowd, and I went to the next telephone.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And I called my parents at home.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And my mother was a bit panicky-- my stepmother that-- of course, what I called her mother, of course.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
